Alembic migrations for FORGE Engine
===================================

The schema is versioned here. `Base.metadata.create_all` (in core/database.py)
still runs on app startup for zero-config first boot, but migrations are the
authoritative record for upgrading an existing database.

The DB URL is resolved by env.py: $FORGE_DATABASE_URL if set, else the app's
configured DATABASE_PATH (see core/config.py). Run all commands from
apps/forge-engine with the package importable, e.g. `PYTHONPATH=src`.

Common commands
---------------
  # Apply all migrations to the configured DB
  PYTHONPATH=src alembic upgrade head

  # Create a new migration after changing models
  PYTHONPATH=src alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

  # Inspect / roll back
  PYTHONPATH=src alembic current
  PYTHONPATH=src alembic downgrade -1

Existing database created by create_all
---------------------------------------
If a DB already exists from a pre-Alembic build, mark it as up-to-date without
re-running the initial migration:

  PYTHONPATH=src alembic stamp head

Drift guard
-----------
tests/test_migrations.py fails if models and migrations diverge — always
generate a migration when you add or change a model.
